{
  "dialogueGraphs": [
    {
      "id": "DG_SCN069_COPIER_EVIDENCE_PACKET",
      "sceneId": "SCN-069",
      "startNodeId": "N_START_01",
      "nodes": [
        {
          "id": "N_START_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "conditions": [
            {
              "key": "act3.evidencePacketCompiled",
              "op": "==",
              "value": false
            },
            {
              "key": "act3.recordsEvidenceCollected",
              "op": "==",
              "value": true
            }
          ],
          "text": "The Copy and Fax Room smells like warm plastic and old toner.\nThe copier\u2019s control panel is lit, patient, and already disappointed in you.",
          "next": "N_START_02"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_START_02",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You have the records evidence.\nWhat you don\u2019t have is a packet someone else can sign without becoming a story.",
          "next": "N_PANEL_01"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_PANEL_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The screen offers three big buttons: COPY, SCAN, and \u201cCOMPLIANCE DUPLICATION (LEGACY).\u201d\nUnder them, a smaller note: \u201cDO NOT CREATE NEW INFORMATION.\u201d\nSomeone has underlined it hard enough to dent the plastic.",
          "next": "N_PANEL_02"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_PANEL_02",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The copier beeps once\u2014an opinion.\nOn-screen: \u201cSELECT SOURCE MATERIAL.\u201d\nBelow that: \u201cORIGINALS ONLY.\u201d\nBelow that, smaller: \u201cDO NOT FEED ORIGINALS.\u201d\n\nA problem designed by committee, maintained by habit.",
          "next": "N_PANEL_03"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_PANEL_03",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "It waits for a choice like an auditor.",
          "next": "PC_MAIN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_MAIN_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "USE_COMPILE",
              "text": "use: Compile Evidence Packet section.",
              "next": "PC_COMPILE_APPROACH_STD"
            },
            {
              "id": "USE_TEST",
              "text": "use: Run a test page first.",
              "next": "N_TEST_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "LOOK_CHECKLIST",
              "text": "look: Review the packet checklist posted on the wall.",
              "next": "N_CHECKLIST_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "USE_SERVICE_CODE",
              "text": "use: Use service code / compliance duplication mode.",
              "checks": [
                {
                  "type": "faction",
                  "faction": "OLEA"
                }
              ],
              "onPassNext": "N_COMPLIANCE_01",
              "onFailNext": "N_SERVICE_DENIED_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "USE_FAX_REDUNDANCY",
              "text": "use: Fax it \u201cfor redundancy.\u201d",
              "next": "N_FAX_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "ASK_WHICH",
              "text": "ask: \u201cWhich is it.\u201d",
              "next": "N_WHICH_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "LOOK_STICKERS",
              "text": "look: Service code sticker stack.",
              "next": "N_STICKERS_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "LOOK_FAX_TRAY",
              "text": "look: Fax machine tray.",
              "next": "N_FAXTRAY_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "LOOK_BINDER_SHELF",
              "text": "look: Binder supplies shelf.",
              "next": "N_SHELF_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE",
              "text": "leave: Step away.",
              "next": "N_LEAVE_01"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_WHICH_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The copier does not answer questions.\nIt waits for a choice like an auditor who already wrote the finding.",
          "next": "PC_MAIN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_STICKERS_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "A neat stack of peel-off stickers: SERVICE ACCESS / CALIBRATION / AUDIT OVERRIDE (EXPIRED).\nThey\u2019re numbered in a way that implies a calendar you are not invited to see.",
          "next": "PC_MAIN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_FAXTRAY_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The fax tray holds a single curled confirmation page from years ago.\nIt reads: \u201cTRANSMISSION PARTIAL \u2014 RECEIPT SUCCESSFUL.\u201d\nSomeone circled \u201cSUCCESSFUL\u201d like it won an argument.",
          "next": "PC_MAIN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_SHELF_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Three-ring binders, divider tabs, and a label maker with the tape compartment open.\nThere are exactly two fonts available: \u201cOFFICIAL\u201d and \u201cOFFICIAL (CONDENSED).\u201d\nThe second one looks nervous.",
          "next": "PC_MAIN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_CHECKLIST_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "A laminated checklist hangs beside the panel, edges browned from fluorescent light.\nLine 4 reads: \u201cCross-check identifiers, dates, and recurring charges.\u201d\nLine 5 reads: \u201cDo not editorialize. Editorialization is discoverable.\u201d\n\nIn pen, someone added: \u201cIf it feels like a story, it isn\u2019t evidence.\u201d\nThe handwriting gets smaller on the last words, like it\u2019s trying not to be quoted.",
          "next": "PC_CHECKLIST_BACK"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_CHECKLIST_BACK",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK",
              "text": "leave: Back to the panel.",
              "next": "PC_MAIN_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_TEST_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You feed a blank sheet. Your hand hesitates for no reason you\u2019d put in writing.\nThe machine pulls it in like it\u2019s taking custody.",
          "next": "N_TEST_02"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_TEST_02",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "It prints: \u201cTEST PAGE \u2014 NOT RECORD.\u201d\nIn the corner: a timestamp accurate to the second, as if daring you to dispute it.\n\nThe copier is warmed up. The room is, too, in its own quiet way.",
          "next": "PC_TEST_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_TEST_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "USE_COMPILE_NOW",
              "text": "use: Compile Evidence Packet section.",
              "next": "PC_COMPILE_APPROACH_STD"
            },
            {
              "id": "USE_SERVICE_CODE_NOW",
              "text": "use: Use service code / compliance duplication mode.",
              "checks": [
                {
                  "type": "faction",
                  "faction": "OLEA"
                }
              ],
              "onPassNext": "N_COMPLIANCE_01",
              "onFailNext": "N_SERVICE_DENIED_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK",
              "text": "leave: Back to the panel menu.",
              "next": "PC_MAIN_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_SERVICE_DENIED_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The panel requests an authorization code you do not possess.\nIt offers a helpful explanation: \u201cUNAUTHORIZED USE CREATES DISCOVERABLE INTENT.\u201d",
          "next": "PC_SERVICE_DENIED_BACK"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_SERVICE_DENIED_BACK",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK",
              "text": "leave: \u201cFine.\u201d",
              "next": "PC_MAIN_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_COMPLIANCE_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You peel a SERVICE ACCESS sticker. The adhesive resists, personally.\nThe panel accepts the code without gratitude.",
          "next": "N_COMPLIANCE_02"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_COMPLIANCE_02",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "New options appear: \u201cWATERMARK: WORKING COPY,\u201d \u201cAUTO-REDACT PERSONAL,\u201d \u201cMATCH LEDGER FORMAT.\u201d\nNone of them are about truth. All of them are about survivability.",
          "next": "PC_COMPLIANCE_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_COMPLIANCE_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "USE_COMPILE",
              "text": "use: Compile Evidence Packet section.",
              "next": "PC_COMPILE_APPROACH_COMP"
            },
            {
              "id": "USE_TEST",
              "text": "use: Run a test page first.",
              "next": "N_TESTC_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_TO_STANDARD",
              "text": "leave: Return to standard menu.",
              "next": "PC_MAIN_MENU"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE",
              "text": "leave: Step away.",
              "next": "N_LEAVE_01"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_TESTC_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "In compliance mode, even a blank page feels like a form.\nThe machine prints: \u201cTEST PAGE \u2014 NOT RECORD,\u201d then adds a subtle watermark you didn\u2019t ask for.",
          "next": "PC_TESTC_BACK"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_TESTC_BACK",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "USE_COMPILE",
              "text": "use: Compile Evidence Packet section.",
              "next": "PC_COMPILE_APPROACH_COMP"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK",
              "text": "leave: Back.",
              "next": "PC_COMPLIANCE_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_COMPILE_APPROACH_STD",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "USE_CAREFUL",
              "text": "use: Compile carefully (cross-check identifiers, dates, recurring charges).",
              "next": "N_COMPILE_CAREFUL_STD_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "USE_FAST",
              "text": "use: Compile fast (accept defaults).",
              "next": "N_COMPILE_FAST_STD_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK",
              "text": "leave: Not yet.",
              "next": "PC_MAIN_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_COMPILE_APPROACH_COMP",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "USE_CAREFUL",
              "text": "use: Compile carefully (use compliance formatting, verify every field).",
              "next": "N_COMPILE_CAREFUL_COMP_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "USE_FAST",
              "text": "use: Compile fast (let compliance mode decide).",
              "next": "N_COMPILE_FAST_COMP_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK",
              "text": "leave: Not yet.",
              "next": "PC_COMPLIANCE_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_COMPILE_CAREFUL_STD_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You lay out the records evidence and build a packet that can\u2019t be argued with easily.\nIdentifiers. Dates. Recurring charges.\nThe same numbers showing up where they shouldn\u2019t.",
          "next": "N_COMPILE_PRINT_01"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_COMPILE_FAST_STD_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You accept the defaults and start feeding the machine what it wants.\nIf anything is wrong, it will be wrong in a standard way.\nSometimes that passes as defensible.",
          "next": "N_COMPILE_PRINT_01"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_COMPILE_CAREFUL_COMP_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You let compliance mode format the output, but you don\u2019t let it think for you.\nYou verify every identifier, every date, every repeating charge.\nSurvivability without improvisation.",
          "next": "N_COMPILE_PRINT_01"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_COMPILE_FAST_COMP_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You let compliance mode decide.\nIt watermarks what it can, redacts what it thinks is personal, and aligns everything to the ledger\u2019s idea of reality.\nIt\u2019s not truth. It\u2019s presentation with guardrails.",
          "next": "N_COMPILE_PRINT_01"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_COMPILE_PRINT_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The copier pulls page after page, stamping the corner with a bland, official certainty.\nThe sound is steady.\nYour jaw isn\u2019t.",
          "next": "N_COMPILE_PRINT_02"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_COMPILE_PRINT_02",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "A divider tab prints last: \u201cEVIDENCE PACKET \u2014 RECORDS.\u201d\nThe label maker chooses \u201cOFFICIAL (CONDENSED)\u201d without asking.",
          "next": "N_OUTCOME_CONFIRM_01"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_OUTCOME_CONFIRM_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The section is compiled, hole-punched, and binder-ready.\nYou can almost hear someone else agreeing with it later, because it\u2019s easier than disagreeing.\n\nYou stop one step short of calling it complete.",
          "next": "END_COMPILED"
        },
        {
          "id": "END_COMPILED",
          "type": "end",
          "outcomeId": "compile_evidence_packet",
          "effects": [
            {
              "key": "act3.evidencePacketCompiled",
              "action": "set",
              "value": true
            },
            {
              "key": "inventory.items",
              "action": "add",
              "value": "ITEM_EVIDENCE_PACKET_SECTION"
            },
            {
              "key": "paperwork.completeness",
              "action": "increment",
              "value": 2
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_FAX_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You lift the handset and feed the first page like you\u2019re making a backup of your own conscience.\nThe machine whines.\n\nThe tray spits a status slip that manages to be both reassuring and useless:\n\u201cTRANSMISSION PARTIAL \u2014 RECEIPT SUCCESSFUL.\u201d\n\nYou didn\u2019t create redundancy.\nYou created another version of events.",
          "next": "PC_FAX_BACK"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_FAX_BACK",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK",
              "text": "leave: Put the handset back.",
              "next": "PC_MAIN_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_LEAVE_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You step back. The copier\u2019s screen stays lit, like it\u2019s keeping your place in line.\nThe room does not forget unfinished tasks.\n\nNothing is compiled. Nothing is defensible yet.",
          "next": "END_NO_ACTION"
        },
        {
          "id": "END_NO_ACTION",
          "type": "end"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
